description: From in- (prefix meaning ‘in, into; towards’) +‎ flood (“overflow of water from a lake or other body of water; flowing in of the tide; to overflow; to cover or partly fill as if by a flood”).

entries.meaning: The act or process of flooding or flowing in; an inflow or influx.

verbs.description: inflood (third-person singular simple present infloods, present participle inflooding, simple past and past participle inflooded)

entries.meaning: (transitive) Of a river, water, etc.: to flood or flow into (a place).
(intransitive) To flood or flow in; to inflow.
